be looking for a Pyrolisk in short order.  Lastly, you need a mage to enchant 
an Item to forge the object into the desired form.  To this end, I am making a 
hammer as a gift to you and am enclosing the directions on its use, so that a 
lesser mage can bind the magic to the item in question.  The main part to 
remember is that once you put the components on the anvil, a mage must use the
hammer to forge the components together.  This will release the spell I have 
ingrained into the hammer and the object of you interest will be formed.
  Also, many valuable items can be joined to form an even more valuable item.
The only way to be figure out the right combination is by experimentation.

                                                    Signed, Marcus

